I have analyzed the feedback from Cycle 7 and will address the layout and visual issues at the bottom of the homepage. My course of action is to fix the cut-off title, remove visual artifacts, reduce empty space, and correctly position the footer content.

1.  **Fix Mission Section Layout (`src/components/global/lamp.tsx`):**
    *   To fix the cut-off title and reduce the large empty space, I will significantly decrease the vertical padding and minimum height of the `LampContainer`.
    *   I will also adjust the vertical translation (`-translate-y-`) of the lamp's light source and motion elements, moving them higher to create more room for the title.
    *   To eliminate the rectangular visual artifacts, I will remove the `div` elements that use large blur effects (`blur-2xl`, `blur-3xl`), as these are creating the unwanted shapes.
    *   I will also expand the width of the conic gradient motion divs to ensure the light effect feels expansive and covers the area properly.

2.  **Clean up `src/components/home/MissionSection.tsx`:**
    *   I will remove the negative margin (`-mb-40`) that was previously added. The layout adjustments in `lamp.tsx` provide a cleaner solution for managing the space between this section and the footer.

3.  **Reposition Footer Content (`src/components/layout/Footer.tsx`):**
    *   To align the footer text to the corners, I will restructure the component. Instead of a single centered container, I will use a full-width flex container with `justify-between`.
    *   This will allow the two text blocks to be pushed to the left and right edges of the viewport, with appropriate padding to keep them from touching the absolute corners.

<course_of_action>
1.  **Update `src/components/global/lamp.tsx`:**
    *   Reduce `min-h` and `pb` (padding-bottom) to decrease the overall height of the section.
    *   Increase the negative `translate-y` values for the lamp's core elements to move the light source up and prevent it from obscuring the title.
    *   Remove the `div`s with `blur-2xl` and `blur-3xl` classes that are causing the rectangular artifacts.
    *   Widen the conic gradient `motion.div` elements to create a smoother, more expansive lighting effect.
2.  **Update `src/components/home/MissionSection.tsx`:**
    *   Remove the `className="-mb-40"` from the `section` element to let the updated `LampContainer` manage the spacing naturally.
3.  **Update `src/components/layout/Footer.tsx`:**
    *   Replace the main `div`'s `container` class with classes for a full-width flexbox layout (`w-full`, `flex`, `justify-between`, `items-center`, `px-8`).
    *   Remove the now-unnecessary inner wrapper `div`.
    *   Adjust the text alignment and padding on the child `p` tags to ensure they align correctly to the left and right.
</course_of_action>

