10.content:
I have analyzed the feedback and the provided screenshots. My course of action is to address the layout and styling issues at the bottom of the homepage, focusing on the mission section and the footer. I will fix the cut-off title, remove the visual artifacts in the lamp effect, reduce the empty space above the footer, and correctly align the footer text to the corners.

1.  **Fix Cut-off Title and Visual Artifacts:** I will modify `src/components/global/lamp.tsx`.
    *   To fix the rectangular artifacts and give the lamp's light effect more room to blend smoothly, I will increase the minimum height of the `LampContainer` to fill the screen's height (`min-h-screen`).
    *   To prevent the title from being cut off at the top, I will adjust the vertical positioning of the content within the `LampContainer`, bringing it down slightly.

2.  **Reduce Empty Space Above Footer:** The large gap between the "Read Our Mission" button and the footer is caused by excessive bottom padding within the `LampContainer`. I will remove this large padding from `src/components/global/lamp.tsx` to shrink the empty space.

3.  **Correct Footer Alignment:** I will update `src/components/layout/Footer.tsx` to achieve the desired corner-aligned layout. I will refactor the flexbox container to ensure it justifies its content to the space between, pushing the "source code" text to the left and the copyright text to the right on all screen sizes.

<course_of_action>
1.  **Update `src/components/global/lamp.tsx`:**
    *   Increase the `LampContainer`'s minimum height to `min-h-screen` to expand the particle and lamp effect area, which will resolve the hard-edged rectangular artifacts.
    *   Remove the large bottom padding (`pb-40`) to reduce the empty space below the content.
    *   Adjust the vertical translation of the content wrapper from `-translate-y-80` to a smaller value like `-translate-y-72` to lower the content and prevent the title from being cut off.
2.  **Update `src/components/home/MissionSection.tsx`:**
    *   Remove the aggressive negative bottom margin (`-mb-40`) which is no longer necessary after adjusting the `LampContainer`'s height and padding.
3.  **Update `src/components/layout/Footer.tsx`:**
    *   Simplify the flexbox layout within the footer's main container to `flex flex-row items-center justify-between`.
    *   Remove the unnecessary wrapping `div` and responsive classes (`flex-col`, `md:flex-row`).
    *   Ensure the two text elements are direct children of the container and have `text-left` and `text-center` (or `md:text-right`) alignment respectively, forcing them to opposite sides.
</course_of_action>

